<DOC><DOCNO> AP890421-0224 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-21-89 0916EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-GM-Perkins     04-21 0146</FIRST><SECOND>BC-GM-Perkins,0153</SECOND><HEAD>Perkins Named General Manager</HEAD><DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   James C. Perkins was named general manager ofGeneral Motors Corp.'s Chevrolet Division, succeeding retiringexecutive Bob Burger.   Perkins, who also will become a vice president, takes over asChevrolet's general manager May 1 when Burger, 64, retires. Theannouncement was made Thursday.   Perkins, 54, returned to GM earlier this year after four yearsat Toyota Motors Sales, U.S.A. As senior vice president there,Perkins was in charge of the company's new Lexus luxury cardivision.   Perkins joined GM in 1960 in the Chevrolet zone office in Dallasand was named general sales manager for GM's Buick Division in1982. When he returned to GM from Toyota, Perkins was namedassistant general manager for Chevrolet.   Burger joined Chevrolet in 1949 and became a GM vice presidentin 1977. He was named Chevrolet's general manager in 1984.</TEXT></DOC>